$M^{-1} = \frac {-a}{b(na+b)}U + \frac 1b I$.
$$M^n = \frac {(na+b)^n-b^n}nU + b^nI  \Rightarrow 
             \left\{
             \begin{array} {ll}
             n \text{ pair }  &: a = 0, \text{ ou }
                                       -\frac{\smash{2b}}n,\ b = \pm1 \cr
                    n \text{ impair} &: a = 0,\ b = 1. \cr
                    \end{array}\right.$$
